bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Rebecca Craighill Lancefield, researcher in bacteriology at The Rockefeller University from 1925 worked on immunochemical studies of streptococci and the chemical composition and antigenic structure of hemolytic streptococci. Her classification system of hemolytic streptococci, known universally as The Lancefield Group, has served to illuminate the biology of these organisms and the mechanisms by which they produce disease.
